<item>
            <title>[SWF-75] Context relative redirect after flow completion</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SWF-75</link>
                <project id="10050" key="SWF">Spring Web Flow</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The redirect: prefix isn&apos;t currently usable from an end-state (as it attempts to do a conversation redirect - which is not supported from a end-state) &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;it is resulting in a NPE&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
Achieving a context relative redirect from an end-state using the externalRedirect: prefix is possible, but the syntax is not very nice.&lt;br/&gt;
The suggestion is to use the redirect: prefix from an end-state to perform a context relative redirect after flow completion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please see this thread details: &lt;a href=&quot;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=23020&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://forum.springframework.org/showthread.php?t=23020&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
